  "prompt": "Why do I keep getting fleas from my dogs?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why you might keep getting fleas from your dogs:\n\n1. Incomplete flea treatment\n- Not treating all pets in the household\n- Using ineffective flea prevention methods\n- Inconsistent treatment schedule\n\n2. Environment issues\n- Flea eggs and larvae in carpets, bedding, and furniture\n- Yard or outdoor areas with flea populations\n- Warm, humid conditions that promote flea reproduction\n\n3. Inadequate home cleaning\n- Not vacuuming frequently\n- Not washing pet bedding in hot water\n- Not treating your home environment for fleas\n\n4. Pet exposure\n- Dogs picking up fleas from other animals\n- Frequent walks in areas with high flea populations\n- Interaction with wildlife or stray animals\n\nTo address the issue:\n- Use veterinarian-recommended flea prevention for all pets\n- Regularly wash and treat pet bedding\n- Vacuum frequently and dispose of vacuum bags\n- Consider professional pest control treatment\n- Use indoor and outdoor flea treatments\n- Maintain year-round flea prevention\n\nIf the problem persists, consult your veterinarian for personalized advice and potential underlying issues.",
